Package: cl-acl-compat
Version: 1.2.35
Revision: 1
Description: Allegro Common Lisp compatability library
License: LGPL
Maintainer: Lars Rosengreen <lars@margay.org>

Type: cl

Depends: clc, clisp-clc | cmucl-clc | openmcl-clc | sbcl-clc, cl-puri, cl-ppcre

Source: mirror:sourceforge:portableaserve/portableaserve-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: c7fc8af81f003c27ee7596f7fd2b242a

SourceDirectory: portableaserve

CompileScript: /usr/bin/true

InstallScript: <<
  find . -type d -exec chmod 755 {} \;
  find . -type f -exec chmod 644 {} \;
  mkdir -p %i/share/common-lisp/source/acl-compat
  cp -Rp acl-compat/* %i/share/common-lisp/source/acl-compat
  mkdir -p %i/share/common-lisp/systems
  ln -s %p/share/common-lisp/source/acl-compat/acl-compat.asd %i/share/common-lisp/systems/acl-compat.asd
<<

PostInstScript: %p/sbin/register-common-lisp-source acl-compat
PreRmScript: %p/sbin/unregister-common-lisp-source acl-compat

DocFiles: acl-compat/ChangeLog acl-compat/README aserve/license-lgpl.txt

DescDetail: << 
acl-compat is a library that implements parts of the Allegro Common
Lisp (ACL) API for areas that are not covered by the ANSI Common Lisp
standard itself (e.g. sockets, threading).  The motivation for
creating and maintaining acl-compat is to get the web server
AllegroServe (that was released by Franz Inc under the LLGPL) running
on a wide range of Lisp implementations, with as few source changes to
its core code as possible.
<<

DescUsage: <<
(asdf:oos 'asdf:load-op 'acl-compat)
<<

Homepage: http://portableaserve.sourceforge.net/

